No. The inject command hard-exits at line `inject.rs:273-275` if the project DB doesn't exist:

```rust
let db_path = project_db_path(&root);
if !db_path.exists() {
    return Ok(());
}
```

It silently returns nothing — no indexing, no wiki generation, no side effects. The inject hook is a pure read-only consumer; it only works if a database already exists.

To bootstrap a new project you need to run `proactive-context init` first, which starts the background daemon that watches and indexes markdown files. Wiki guides are generated separately via the capture hook (`proactive-context capture` on session end). Inject is downstream of all that.
